I"ÎD<p><img src="/assets/img/vim/vim-c-cpp-en.jpg" alt="How to Customize Your VIM From Zero to C/C++ (Ubuntu Cinnamon)" /></p>

<p>In these article we install plugins for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Autocomplete for <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/why-is-the-c-programming-language-still-on-the-rise/">C</a>/<a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/drogon-cpp-the-fastest-web-framework-in-the-world/">C++</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/install-colorscheme-terroo-colors-on-your-vim/">Color Themes</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/install-in-your-preferred-editor-an-auto-complete-with-artificial-intelligence/">Autocomplete with Articial Intelligence and Machine Learning</a></li>
  <li>Powerline for <a href="https://github.com/vim-airline/vim-airline">Vim Airline</a></li>
  <li>Mappings</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/100-tips-for-the-vim-editor/">Vim editor settings</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/best-alternatives-for-sharing-code-snippets/">Snippets</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/terroo/fonts">Fonts</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/MaskRay/ccls">Language Server</a></li>
  <li>In addition to additional Tips</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
  <p>The procedures were performed on <a href="https://ubuntucinnamon.org/">Ubuntu Cinnamon</a></p>
</blockquote>

